{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"iddd50b2e9-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s5253"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5253"},"text":"§ 5253.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Emergency treatment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"All provisions of this chapter are designated as an emergency requirement and necessary to meet emergency needs pursuant to section 204(a) of S. Con. Res ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"idref":"fn002468"},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"type":"footnote","id":"fn002468"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":" So in original. Probably should be followed by a period."}],"tail":" 21 (110th Congress), the concurrent resolution on the budget for fiscal year 2008 and rescissions of any amounts provided in this chapter shall not be counted for purposes of budget enforcement."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"iddd50b2ea-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/343/dA/tII/s204"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–343, div. A, title II, § 204","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2008-10-03"},"text":"Oct. 3, 2008","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/122/3801"},"text":"122 Stat. 3801","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"iddd50b2eb-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"iddd50b2ec-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"iddd50b2ed-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"This chapter, referred to in text, was in the original “this Act” and was translated as reading “this division”, meaning div. A of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/343"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–343","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2008-10-03"},"text":"Oct. 3, 2008","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/122/3765"},"text":"122 Stat. 3765","children":[],"tail":", known as the Emergency Economic Stabilization Act of 2008, to reflect the probable intent of Congress. For complete classification of division A to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s5201"},"text":"section 5201 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"S. Con. Res. 21 (110th Congress), referred to in text, is S. Con. Res. 21, ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2007-05-17"},"text":"May 17, 2007","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/121/2590"},"text":"121 Stat. 2590","children":[],"tail":", which is not classified to the Code."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
